div.p:
As I lay thus the thought entered my mind, that escape was possible. I might try;
                  if they did catch me, they would only bring me back, and guard me more securely.
                  Why not try it? My mind was made up instantly.

As soon as I was sure that he was too drunk to create any alarm, I quickly arose
                  from my painful position, and turned in the direction of the Union encampment,
                  which I reached two hours before sunrise.
